stylometry: When you have a waiting line in a store, depending on the length of the line and the length of time people spend in it, you may find yourself loosing business to those customers unwilling to wait for your services. So managers must look at the costs associated with queuing, as well as the cost of keeping too many employees on hand. Overall, the best outcome should be reached to minimize cost by deciding the optimum number of employees to keep working on any given day, as well as minimizing queue time for the customers to avoid loosing business. (These numbers will vary widely from business to business depending on what kind of services are being offered and how long people are willing to wait for them.)
